name: Ferns
friendly_name: Ferns, horsetails, quillworts, lycopods, and relatives
notable_exceptions: Some seed plants have very frilly, highly dissected leaves that resemble ferns.

name: Woody Plants
notable_exceptions: Some small, low-lying shrubs can be mistaken for herbaceous plants.

name: Graminoids
friendly_name: Grasses, sedges, and other plants with long, narrow leaves
key_characteristics: narrow leaves that sheath the stem, and small, inconspicuous flowers
notable_exceptions: Some non-grasses have very narrow leaves, but produce showy flowers

name: Aquatic Plants
friendly_name: Plants with most of their parts submerged under water
key_characteristics: specialized leaves and tissues that can withstand flooding
notable_exceptions: Some upland plants can be flooded temporarily but are not specialized for living under water

name: Monocots
friendly_name: Lilies, orchids, irises, aroids, and other monocots
key_characteristics: seedlings have a single cotyledon (embryo leaf); plants have  flower parts in multiples of 3, parallel-veined leaves
notable_exceptions: Grasses are also monocots but may be classified here under "grass-like plants."

name: Non-Monocots
friendly_name: Asters and all other flowering dicots
key_characteristics: flowering plants without parallel leaf veins, and flower parts usually in multiples of 2 or 5
notable_exceptions: This is a large group that contains many species that vary widely in characteristics
